<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,445,543]" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">
This brachypterous genus contains only the 
<typeStatus box="[689,737,481,507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">type</typeStatus>
species, and very similar to previous genus as 
<emphasis box="[1257,1364,482,507]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">mexicana</emphasis>
group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1901" box="[181,308,517,543]" class="Insecta" family="Chorotypidae" genus="Anabropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[181,308,517,543]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">Anabropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but should not be synonymized to retain the distinction between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1988" box="[1045,1217,517,543]" class="Insecta" family="Chorotypidae" genus="Pteranabropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1045,1217,517,543]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">Pteranabropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1901" box="[1271,1398,517,543]" class="Insecta" family="Chorotypidae" genus="Anabropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1398,517,543]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">Anabropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
